This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the performance of deep residual networks on image classification tasks such as CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, and ImageNet. Additionally, the paper proposes a new residual unit that improves generalization, which is a common problem in computer vision tasks.

The paper also discusses the importance of identity mappings in the residual building blocks, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The experiments conducted in the paper also involve training and testing deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.

The paper proposes a new residual unit that improves the performance of deep residual networks, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the results of experiments on image classification tasks, which may also make it relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category, as image classification is a common task in computer vision-based natural language processing.
